üü£ 2. Vector layer reading of Peru 

data("Peru")
peru.region <- Peru %>%
  dplyr::group_by(dep) %>%
  summarise()

glimpse(peru.region)
#> Rows: 25
#> Columns: 2

üü£ 3. Exploration Peru map 

mapview(peru.region,legend = NULL)

üü£ 4. Transformation of sf object to a feature collection 

peru.ee <- peru.region %>%
  pol_as_ee(
    id = c("dep"),
    simplify = 100
    )

üü£ 5. Processing data with innovar 

peru.ndvi <- peru.ee %>%
  get_vegetation(
    from = "2018-01-01",
    to = "2019-12-31",
    band = "NDVI",
    fun = "mean")

peru.def <- peru.ee %>%
  get_def(
    from = "2018-02-01",
    to = "2019-12-31"
    )

peru.pr <- peru.ee %>%
  get_climate(
    from = "2018-02-01",
    to = "2019-12-31",
    by = "month",
    band = "pr",
    fun = "mean"
    )

üü£ 6. Processing data for mapping 

peru.ndvi.sf <- inner_join(peru.region,peru.ndvi,"dep")
peru.pr.sf <- inner_join(peru.region,peru.pr ,"dep")
peru.def.sf <- inner_join(peru.region,peru.def,"dep")

üü£ 11. Mapping climate variables with the innovar theme 

pr.plot <- peru.pr.sf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill=`pr2019-01`)) +
  scale_fill_innova(discrete = FALSE,name="Precipitation") +
  theme_bw()
ndvi.plot<- peru.ndvi.sf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill=`NDVI2019-01`)) +
  scale_fill_innova(discrete = FALSE,name="NDVI") +
  theme_bw()
def.plot <-  peru.def.sf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill=Adef_2019)) +
  scale_fill_innova(discrete = FALSE,name="Deforestation") +
  theme_bw()
